Job Desception:
About the job


230666W-01DescriptionResponsibilities:Corporate Accounting & Reporting (Statutory & Management Reporting) Preparation of quarterly & annual statutory financial statements;Lead & coordinate internal audit;Lead the monthly & annual period end close process for internal financial statements in SAP CentralFinance system;Review & analysis of internal financial statements;Ensure that processes are in place, reviewed and upgraded periodically so that all accounting records are adequately created and maintained and meet statutory & internal reporting requirements;Provide information to facilitate assessment proceedings under various Acts;Review and ensure compliance with the Accounting Standards (IFRS & US GAAP) and other regulations;
Analysis Prepare & share reports required by local, regional & global stakeholders;Prepare P&L variance analysis;Prepare variance & trend analysis on Balance Sheet items;Prepare variance analysis on COGS.
Product Costing Processing and recording of all the transactions relating to inventories, e.g., cost of goods sold/consumed, cost of goods imported/produced, etc.;Ensure that procedures and processes are in place for timely and accurate Product costing as per company policy & local requirements. These processes & procedures are reviewed and upgraded periodically;Ensuring accurate inventory costing;Periodic reconciliation of inventory balances as per record outside the system with record in accounting system for values and with quantitative physical stock reports;Obtain quality results on quarterly basis from QA and after discussion with Manager Accounts record appropriate inventory reserve for obsolete, slow moving items and below standard inventory. Ensure that proper approvals for reserves are obtained as per Delegation of Authority limits before recording these reserves in the system;
Plant/Warehouse Visits   Quarterly visit warehouses to check inventory reporting & other compliances; Providing feedback to Accounting Manager for required improvements, enhancements;
Bank Reconciliations  Review of reconciliation of bank accounts on fortnightly basis to ensure that all the bank transactions have been recorded completely and accurately; Follow-up with vendors for outstanding checks;
Accruals & Prepayments  Perform balance sheet reconciliations as assigned;
Taxation Coordination & Support to Regional Tax TeamSecretarial Compliances  Arrange Board and Members meetings as per statutory and business needs; Ensure maintenance of all records as per applicable Corporate Laws; Ensure timely filing of forms and returns with Registrar of Companies; Ensure compliance with applicable Corporate Laws; Ensure and communicate key changes relating to law / compliances which impact the business.
Internal Controls  Maintain high standards of Internal Control environment specially in relevant areas of responsibility; Adherence to Key Control Activities (KCAs) standards for relevant areas; Lead the Process Mapping exercise & assess controls for other functions as directed by Controllership Leaders;
Innovation, Automation & Paperless Environment  Continuous effort on introducing new initiatives to bring efficiency & effectiveness in the processes; Bring standardization & automation in key tasks;
Professional Development, Etc.  Attend conferences, seminars and workshops; participate in professional organizations, read journals, etc., to maintain competent level of appropriate expertise; Ensure accounting hygiene at work; Any other work to be assigned by the management from time to time;
QualificationsQualifications Education: Qualified Chartered Accountant (CA)/CA Finalist Experience: 2 years post articleship, industry experience in an MNC or well reputed company
Additional Knowledge, Abilities And Key Skills Knowledge of Accounting Standards as applicable in Pakistan, US GAAP and Costing;Knowledge of internal controls, especially financial reporting controlsExcellent communication and Interpersonal skills;Knowledge of Pakistani Tax laws;Knowledge of Corporate laws;Demonstrated skills in conflict resolution and handling objections by taking initiative;Strong analytical skills;Ability to effectively interact with different types/levels of people;Ability to work in a team environment;Ability to learn fast to adapt to new changes;Good command over Microsoft Office Application especially Excel.
